{
  "texts": [
    "Notably, the heavy-hex code is readily implemented on the heavy-hex lattice geometry on which we conducted the experiment.",
    "For each of these injection schemes, we argue that we can detect any single error that may occur.",
    "This is important to maintain the error suppression obtained when preparing the CZ state.In the case of the colour-code state-injection protocol, we inject the error-detecting code described in the main text directly into the larger code.",
    "In the case of the surface code and heavy-hex code, however, we inject a related code, that we call the [[4, 1, 2]] code.",
    "To complete these injection protocols, we need to take the CZ state prepared on the error-detecting code and copy its logical state onto two copies of the [[4, 1, 2]] code."
  ]
}